Dr. Robert Petzel, Under Secretary for Health in the Department of Veterans Affairs, has resigned and his resignation has been accepted by Secretary Shinseki. The President supports Secretary Shinseki's decision and is committed to ensuring that veterans have access to timely and quality healthcare. Secretary Shinseki has been asked to conduct a review of Veterans Health Administration practices and procedures nationwide to improve access to care. The Department of Veterans Affairs is taking steps to ensure that veterans have confidence in and access to the care and benefits they deserve. The allegations of misconduct are being taken seriously and appropriate actions will be taken based on the findings of the independent VA Office of Inspector General investigation. Both the President and Secretary Shinseki thank Dr. Petzel for his years of service to veterans.